# Persistence and state

- `PersistedDesktopState.schemaVersion` is `1`. Changing shape means updating types, defaults, and `validatePersistedState`.
- All durable mutations go through `mergeAndSaveState` / `saveFullState` in `persistence.ts` — persist first, then `set` the store.
- Validate untrusted payloads with `validatePersistedState` (never assume JSON shape).
- Hydrate stores via `useDesktopInit` / store `hydrate` helpers; do not bypass with ad-hoc localStorage writes.
- Empty/corrupt item lists fall back to seed items from `defaultItems.ts`.
- Browser/non-Tauri path uses the `persona5-explorer-launcher-state` localStorage key.
